how much do i really know about horses ive been taking lessons for three years and i did quiet a bit with horses in that time i did a lot of the pat parelli program for those of you who know what that is and learned to ride hunter jumper i love horses a lot but some times i feel i still don't knonw them as well as i'd like i still get scared some times when horses do somthing unexpected but for the most part i can keep a cool head last year a horse i was riding was on some feed that made her crazy i did not know at the time so we went trail riding she reared i did not get scared and i thought i had things under control when she did it again she feel backwords nearly crushing me ever since then before i get on a hose i feel a little jittery but i'm fine once i am up i started questioning everything i know about horses do i really know much at all to get scared like that i should know what to do but i feel like i don't i've spent years around them of those years doing it for a living i have yet to meet someone who knows it all i don't think it's possible on the other hand i've known plenty who laid claim to the title the fact that you've been taking prof training getting back on will do wonders for your confidence healthy respect is always good more confidence will come with time it's been my personal experience that a close call now then keeps you on your toes from being complacent around them you can't take them for granted they're all different and are living creatures with personalities and some even come with baggage lol Social rule Equine conformation Milton H. Erickson Humphrey Bogart Time Out of Mind Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Avenue Q Arabian horse The Emancipation of Mimi Seabiscuit Comanche Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Sin City Little Britain Theory of conduct Jon Secada EastEnders Futurama (TV series - season 2) 2000 Australian Grand Prix Horse tack Kimi Finster Ranma __ characters The Ashlee Simpson Show Characters in the Sm